00:01:26.050 --> 00:01:30.670
And I'll explain what all the
ephemera is that I schlepped

00:01:30.670 --> 00:01:35.020
up to Capitol Hill
bewildering people on Metro.

00:01:35.020 --> 00:01:41.330
So I am a women's history
professor and I am part time at GW,

00:01:41.330 --> 00:01:44.230
part time at Georgetown
for 22 years.

00:01:44.230 --> 00:01:48.860
And my area of interest in women's
history is the women's music

00:01:48.860 --> 00:01:53.860
movement of the 60s, 70s, 80s, 90s.

00:01:53.860 --> 00:01:57.000
And this is a much
misunderstood phenomenon

00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:01.340
which is now just old enough to
start being archived and made

00:02:01.340 --> 00:02:05.280
into a sort of serious
topic of study.

00:02:05.280 --> 00:02:07.210
And it's a very awkward moment

00:02:07.210 --> 00:02:11.630
because there's been critical
backlash against, what are for me,

00:02:11.630 --> 00:02:15.780
very beloved institutions like the
Michigan Womyn's Music Festival

00:02:15.780 --> 00:02:21.090
and a lot of interrogation of
how inclusive women's music was.

00:02:21.090 --> 00:02:26.310
It always has been and we
are also in Washington,

00:02:26.310 --> 00:02:30.860
DC very much connected to
local institutions, people,

00:02:30.860 --> 00:02:35.670
artists that made women's
music the success it is.

00:02:35.670 --> 00:02:39.630
Olivia records was founded
just a few miles from here.

00:02:39.630 --> 00:02:42.840
DC is the base of Sweet
Honey and the Rock,

00:02:42.840 --> 00:02:47.300
which just lost its premier sign
language interpreter Mama Shirley

00:02:47.300 --> 00:02:54.330 position:56%
so we are very sad about her passing
and I dedicate today's talk to her.

00:02:54.330 --> 00:02:58.040
We're located near one of
the best one day festivals

00:02:58.040 --> 00:03:01.670
that was ever organized and
that was SisterFire produced

00:03:01.670 --> 00:03:04.080
by Amy Horowitz and Roadwork.

00:03:04.080 --> 00:03:10.000
Boden Sandstrom started the
first woman sound company here.

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:14.350
This is a really rich region
for looking at people,

00:03:14.350 --> 00:03:17.750
places and things in women's music.

00:03:17.750 --> 00:03:22.680
And what I want to do is try
to make this a more visible

00:03:22.680 --> 00:03:28.720
and serious topic of scholarly
inquiry and popular appreciation.

00:03:28.720 --> 00:03:33.680
And I have been introducing
sound tracks in my lectures

00:03:33.680 --> 00:03:35.940
for a really long time
and travelling

00:03:35.940 --> 00:03:40.000
around the country doing
readings from articles I've done,

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:42.410
interviews with artists, histories

00:03:42.410 --> 00:03:46.170
of different women's
production companies.

00:03:46.170 --> 00:03:52.090
And what I have is only a tiny inch
of what is in my house right now.

00:03:52.090 --> 00:03:53.400
I have one of the best archives

00:03:53.400 --> 00:03:56.910
in the United States
of this whole subject.

00:03:56.910 --> 00:04:02.260
And beginning at the end of January
I was permitted to have a display

00:04:02.260 --> 00:04:07.750
in the Great North Hall of a couple
of glass cases showing a little bit

00:04:07.750 --> 00:04:11.320
of the timeline of
feminist music and sound.

00:04:11.320 --> 00:04:14.170
And I am going to try
and expand on that.

00:04:14.170 --> 00:04:16.680
I brought a few more
things from my house.

00:04:16.680 --> 00:04:21.030
But, at your leisure, you can go
over there and look at what kind

00:04:21.030 --> 00:04:27.010 position:56%
of begins with suffrage protest
music and goes right through to punk

00:04:27.010 --> 00:04:30.210
and there's fantastic items

00:04:30.210 --> 00:04:33.600
from of course the Library
of Congress collection.

00:04:33.600 --> 00:04:38.010
And they include the sheet music
to Loretta Lynn's, The Pill,

00:04:38.010 --> 00:04:44.180
as well as some of the original
albums by Alex Dobkin and some

00:04:44.180 --> 00:04:47.510
of the zines that were
the only media

00:04:47.510 --> 00:04:51.490
to promote women's music,
Hot Wire, Paid My Dues.

00:04:51.490 --> 00:04:56.630
And we also have on display some
