00:15:30.740 --> 00:15:43.680
It's from 1936 and this would
be a woman's penitentiary

00:15:43.680 --> 00:15:51.810
where the women were put at hard
labor and a lot of the songs are

00:15:51.810 --> 00:15:56.710 position:56%
about relationships, people who sold
them out and then there are songs

00:15:56.710 --> 00:16:03.690
that are original, composed behind
bars, and then there are work songs

00:16:03.690 --> 00:16:07.700
that allow women to, like men
on a chain gang or on railroad,

00:16:07.700 --> 00:16:11.430
use rhythm and chanting to
focus on repetitive tasks

00:16:11.430 --> 00:16:12.730
